From 660f7159ae093a2c42e7bc8d68a940d910c9eb54 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Petry <dpetry@anaconda.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Oct 2024 17:31:26 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 21/23] Add missing includes in c10d control_plane Handlers.hpp

Handlers.cpp uses std::unordered_map and std::vector, but the header does
not include them. It won't compile for osx-arm64 metal builds; other
platforms only get away with it through transitive includes.

Taken from AnacondaRecipes/pytorch-feedstock (originally
recipe/patches/0008-add-missing-includes.patch).
---
 torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/control_plane/Handlers.hpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/control_plane/Handlers.hpp b/torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/control_plane/Handlers.hpp
index 58ae9368ea2..48551cbf17a 100644
--- a/torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/control_plane/Handlers.hpp
+++ b/torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/control_plane/Handlers.hpp
@@ -3,7 +3,9 @@
 #include <functional>
 #include <map>
 #include <string>
+#include <unordered_map>
 #include <utility>
+#include <vector>
 
 #include <c10/macros/Export.h>
 
